## PHASE 4 — Deploy to Vercel (5 min)

1. Go to **vercel.com**, make sure you're logged in
2. Click **Add New → Project**
3. You'll see your GitHub repositories listed — click **Import** next to `network-tool`
4. On the Configure screen, check these settings:
   - Framework Preset: **Create React App**
   - Root Directory: `./` (leave as default)
   - Build Command: `npm run build` (leave as default)
   - Output Directory: `build` (leave as default)
5. Click **Deploy**
6. Wait 2–4 minutes. When you see **Congratulations** — you're live
7. Click **Visit** to open your dashboard
8. Copy the URL (looks like `network-tool-yourname.vercel.app`)

**Share that URL with your team. Anyone can open it in any browser, no login needed.**

---

## PHASE 5 — How Your Team Uses the Dashboard

### Path A — Building a new network from scratch (e.g. Bars launch)
1. Open the dashboard URL
2. Click **New Project**
3. Enter project name (e.g. "Protein Bars Launch") and go-live date
4. Select only the Functions you need — e.g. uncheck **Product/NPD** since recipe is done, keep Design, Procurement, Production, Overall Launch Plan
5. Within each Function, uncheck any specific activities not needed
6. Add any custom rows your project needs that aren't in the base template
7. Enter your start date (or toggle to back-calculate from go-live)
8. Click **Generate Network** — full table with all dates builds instantly
9. Critical path and Gantt/Flowchart auto-populate

### Path B — Starting from an existing Excel
1. Open the dashboard URL
2. Click **Upload Excel** → select your network file
3. Dashboard imports all rows and builds the full table
4. From here, add rows, delete rows, change SPOCs, update dates — all inside the dashboard
5. Every edit instantly updates the critical path, Gantt, and flowchart

### Editing the network (works the same for both paths)

| What you want to do | How to do it |
|---|---|
| Edit a task name or SPOC | Click the cell — type the new value |
| Change a TAT | Click the Working Days cell — type new number — dates cascade automatically |
| Mark something as delayed | Fill in the Revised End Date cell — Delay Days auto-calculates |
| Update status | Click the Status cell — pick from the dropdown |
| Add a new activity | Click "+ Add Row" at the bottom of any Sub-Function section |
| Delete an activity | Click the trash icon on the row |
| See critical path update | Happens automatically after every edit — no button to click |
| Switch between Gantt and Flowchart | Toggle button at top of Critical Path module |

### Module quick reference

| Module | What it does |
|---|---|
| Network Builder | Build or upload network → edit everything inline → dates cascade automatically |
| Critical Path | Toggle between Gantt timeline and swimlane flowchart → crash analysis panel |
| Dashboard | RAG status per phase → SPOC workload → delay impact calculator → days to go-live |
| Reminders | Tasks due in 7 days → generate AI reminder email drafts → copy and send |

